  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are caught in heavy short gamma territory with SPX at 6815.85, sitting right between massive negative gamma walls at 6810 (-63.5B) and 6815 (-50.3B), forcing them to buy this breakout move aggressively as they chase delta hedges higher. The regime is fully BREAKOUT with dealers amplifying momentum in both directions - they'll continue buying rallies toward the 6830 positive gamma ceiling where selling pressure kicks in, while any dip back toward 6800-6810 will trigger more dealer buying support. Watch 6830 as the critical flip level where dealer flow reverses from buying to selling, and monitor the 6800-6810 zone as the key amplified support cluster.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect continued upside momentum with dealers buying the breakout, but watch for resistance around 6830.",
